    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-04-17T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-04-17T10:00:00-05:00" n="517"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d517">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1111 <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_BCC1"
                        >Baker, Charles</persName>/71: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1"
                            type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary
                            of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-04-17T23:00:00+08:00"
                            >April 17, 1932—11 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 18—3 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your 144, April 16, 7 p.m. The following has just been received from Hankow:
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“April 16, 2 p.m. My April 16, noon.<note n="37" xml:id="d517fn37">Not
                                printed.</note>
                            <list>
                                <label>1.</label>
                                <item>I earnestly hope that there will be no publicity given matters
                                    mentioned in paragraphs 1 and 7 of your April 15, 11 a.m. ‘Such
                                    publicity at this time would be disastrous.</item>
                                <label>2.</label>
                                <item>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_SSJH1">Sir John Hope
                                        Simpson</persName> and <persName
                                        corresp="frus1932v03#p_AGF1">Andrew</persName> arrived this
                                    morning and have just called on me for detailed discussion of
                                    plans for <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_BCC1"
                                        >Baker</persName>’s release. <persName
                                        corresp="frus1932v03#p_AGF1">Andrew</persName> will have
                                    charge of the negotiations and will offer to <persName
                                        corresp="frus1932v03#p_BCC1">Baker</persName>’s captors
                                    additional dike reconstruction worth up to a limit of 500 tons
                                    of wheat for <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_BCC1"
                                        >Baker</persName>’s release. The Communists are hungry and
                                    the plan offers some hope of success because of the splendid
                                    qualifications of <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_AGF1"
                                        >Andrew</persName>. This chance for success depends a good
                                    deal on our avoiding any misstep. I believe our wisest course
                                    now is to be quiet and watch developments.”</item>
                            </list>
                        </p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
